# Cloudflare Pages — SPA client-side routing fallback.
#
# Without an explicit rule here, Cloudflare falls back to serving 404.html
# for any unmatched path, but it does so with an HTTP 404 status code even
# though the body is the correct app shell. Browsers render the body anyway
# (so manual navigation looks fine), but anything that checks the status
# code first — curl, uptime checks, social-card unfurlers (LinkedIn,
# Slack, iMessage), search engine crawlers — treats the page as broken and
# refuses to render or index it. A shared deep link like /welcome would
# silently 404 for every one of those.
#
# This explicit rule rewrites any unmatched path to index.html and forces
# a 200 status, so /welcome (and any other client-side route) resolves
# correctly regardless of how it's requested. Pages Functions under
# functions/ are matched before _redirects is evaluated, so /api/* routes
# are unaffected by this catch-all.
/*    /index.html   200
